<TITLE> PM to go to Ajmer, not Shantiniketan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 bdnews24.com New Delhi correspondent New Delhi, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina will travel to Ajmer in the Indian state of Rajasthan to offer prayers at the tomb of the Sufi saint Moinuddin Chisti during her visit to India beginning on Sunday. Sources in the Indian government's Ministry of External Affairs said she may travel to Ajmer on Jan 13, after her meetings with Indian prime minister Manmohan Singh, chairperson of the India's ruling Congress-led coalition United Progressive Alliance Sonia Gandhi and others on the first two days of her visit to Delhi. India's finance minister Pranab Mukherjee, external affairs minister S M Krishna and railways minister Mamata Banerjee will also be present during the talks between Hasina and Singh. Krishna, Mukherjee and Banerjee will also call on Hasina separately during her stay in Delhi. Singh will host a banquet in honour of his Bangladeshi counterpart. She will also address a business luncheon hosted by Confederation of Indian Industries (CII), Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce and Industries (FICCI) and Association of Chambers (ASSOCHAM). The prime minister will also call on the Indian president Pratibha Patil She will start her official engagements in Delhi on Monday morning by paying homage to Mahatma Gandhi at his memorial in Rajghat. She will also place wreathes at the memorials of India's former prime ministers Jawaharlal Nehru, Indira Gandhi and Rajiv Gandhi. Hasina traveled to Ajmer and offered prayer at the tomb of Moinuddin Chisti during her earlier visits also. The prime minister, however, will not go to Vishwabharati University at Shantiniketan in the eastern Indian state of West Bengal as was planned earlier. Sources said that West Bengal had been dropped from her itinerary at the request of the Indian government primarily because the university was going through a turmoil due to agitation by the employees and corruption allegation and probe against its vice-chancellor. Hasina is lik